sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Deletes an existing index.

Inputs:

  • Project ID - Unique ID of the project.
  • Index ID - Unique ID of the index.

Outputs:

  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure in Google Cloud Datastore, Status is set to “Error".
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages:

  • Invalid Project ID.
  • Invalid index resource ID.
  • Invalid authorization header. The access token you're using is either expired or invalid.

To use this action, a corresponding Google Cloud Datastore connection and credential must be created and associated with the Google Cloud Datastore Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
sys_hub_action_type_definition.name: Delete Index
